There is no direct implementation of `ListValuedTreeMap` out of the box. To pass concrete implementation of `List` or `Map` into [`ListValuedMap`][2] is intended class [`AbstractListValuedMap`][1]

From javadoc:

&gt; Subclasses specify a Map implementation to use as the internal storage and the List implementation to use as values.

Generic implementation of `ListValuedTreeMap` can be implemented this way:

    public class ListValuedTreeMap&lt;K extends Comparable&lt;K&gt;, V&gt; extends AbstractListValuedMap&lt;K, V&gt; {
        public ListValuedTreeMap() {
            super(new TreeMap&lt;&gt;());
        }

        @Override
        protected List&lt;V&gt; createCollection() {
            return new ArrayList&lt;&gt;();
        }
    }


  [1]: https://commons.apache.org/proper/commons-collections/apidocs/org/apache/commons/collections4/multimap/AbstractListValuedMap.html
